def: Of or pertaining to a tetragon; having four angles or sides;thus, the square, the parallelogram, the rhombus, and the trapeziumare tetragonal fingers.
A smooth triangular area on the inner surface of the bladder,limited by the apertures of the ureters and urethra.
A division of parasitic hemipterous insects, including the truelice. See Illust. in Appendix.
Capable of being prorated, or divided proportionately. [U.S.]

Not combustible; not capable of being burned, decomposed, orconsumed by fire; uninflammable; as, asbestus is an incombustiblesubstance; carbon dioxide is an incombustible gas. Incombustiblecloth, a tissue of amianthus or asbestus; also, a fabric imbued withan incombustible substance.-- In`com*bus"ti*ble*ness, n.-- In`com*bus"ti*bly, adv.
A combination of two or more persons to commit an unlawful act,or to do a lawful act by unlawful means. See Conspiracy.
The act or process of reducing, by depression of temperature orincrease of pressure, etc., to another and denser form, as gas to thecondition of a liquid or steam to water.
A disease occurring in Bengal and other parts of the EastIndies, in which the tongue chaps and cleaves.
A mocking bird. Mocker nut (Bot.), a kind of hickory (Caryatomentosa) and its fruit, which is far inferior to the true shagbarkhickory nut.
